Landry’s Contractors & Docks brand identity should represent a rugged, dependable, and versatile service company capable of handling everything from construction and dock work to transport and property services. The introduction of a bright orange accent should enhance visibility, safety, and brand recognition while maintaining a strong foundation of black, gray, and white. The brand should communicate reliability, hard work, and the ability to “get the job done” across multiple service areas in Jasper and surrounding counties.

Do ✅
Use bright orange (#FF6A00) to represent:
Safety
Action
Visibility on job sites
Keep black and dark gray as the dominant base for a tough, industrial feel
Highlight key elements in orange:
Phone number
Call-to-actions
Logo outlines or borders
Equipment accents (helmets, cones, machinery icons)
Design for real-world use first:
Truck doors & trailers
Equipment decals
Yard signs
Use bold, block-style fonts that are easy to read from a distance
Keep messaging simple and strong:
“Licensed & Insured”
“Dock Sales • Transport • Repair”
Ensure branding works in dusty, outdoor environments (high contrast is key)
Keep a consistent, recognizable logo across all platforms
Don’t ❌
Don’t make orange the main background (too overwhelming, loses professionalism)
Don’t use soft or “clean corporate” colors (this is a rugged service brand)
Don’t clutter designs with too many services listed at once
Don’t use thin fonts or script fonts (hard to read on trucks)
Don’t use multiple shades of orange—stick to one strong tone
Don’t over-design—this brand should feel simple, bold, and tough